[During 2014, Mongolia reported 15 outbreaks of FMD, serotype O. These outbreaks were located in the Dornod, Khentii and Sukhbaatar provinces in the eastern part of the country. See final report and map for this event at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000015019_20140425_170738.pdf.

For background on this event, see comments in ProMED-mail archive numbers 20140429.2438236 and 20140224.2297695.

Khovd province, where the current event occurred, is located in the western part of the country. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khovd_Province

A map of the administrative divisions of Mongolia is available at http://www.ephotopix.com/mongolia_political_map.html. - Mod.CRD

The serotyping and genotyping results are anticipated with interest. During 2013, FMDV serotype A, topotype ASIA, lineage Sea-97 was identified in Mongolia. During 2014, FMDV serotype O, topotype ME-SA, lineage PanAsia was identified. Genotyping data of both are available at http://www.wrlfmd.org/fmd_genotyping/asia/mog.htm. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3212912,1.]
